# 🚀 Node.js Microservices Practice Project (Advanced)

This project demonstrates an **intermediate to advanced microservices architecture** using:

- Node.js  
- Express.js  
- MongoDB (Mongoose)  
- MVC Pattern  
- Validation & Error Handling  

Each service runs independently on a **different port**, follows a **clean architecture**, and connects to **MongoDB**.

This project was developed as part of backend practice tasks during internship training.

---

# 📂 Project Structure

node-microservices-tasks
│
├── inventory-service
│   ├── config/
│   ├── controllers/
│   ├── models/
│   ├── routes/
│   ├── services/
│   ├── middlewares/
│   ├── validators/
│   ├── server.js
│   └── .env
│
├── store-service
│   └── server.js
│
├── course-service
│   └── server.js
│
├── college-service
│   └── server.js
│
├── package.json
└── README.md

Each folder represents a separate microservice.

---

# 🧩 Services Overview

| Service           | Port | Description                         |
|------------------|------|-------------------------------------|
| Inventory Service| 3005 | Advanced CRUD with MongoDB & MVC    |
| Store Service    | 3004 | Store management (CRUD - Express)   |
| Course Service   | 3002 | Manages course data                 |
| College Service  | 3003 | Manages college data                |

---

# 📦 Inventory Service (Advanced)

Base URL:
http://localhost:3005

Features:
- MongoDB integration using Mongoose
- MVC Architecture
- Input validation using express-validator
- Centralized error handling
- Full CRUD operations

Endpoints:

| Method | Endpoint        | Description              |
|--------|---------------|--------------------------|
| GET    | /inventory     | Get all items            |
| GET    | /inventory/:id | Get item by ID           |
| POST   | /inventory     | Create new item          |
| PUT    | /inventory/:id | Update item              |
| DELETE | /inventory/:id | Delete item              |

Example Inventory Object:

{
  "_id": "661234abcd1234",
  "product": "Rice",
  "quantity": 50,
  "storeId": 1,
  "createdAt": "2026-04-07T10:00:00Z",
  "updatedAt": "2026-04-07T10:00:00Z"
}

---

# 🏬 Store Service

Base URL:
http://localhost:3004

Endpoints:

| Method | Endpoint     | Description      |
|--------|-------------|------------------|
| GET    | /stores      | Get all stores   |
| GET    | /stores/:id  | Get store by ID  |
| POST   | /stores      | Create store     |
| PUT    | /stores/:id  | Update store     |
| DELETE | /stores/:id  | Delete store     |

---

# 📚 Course Service

Base URL:
http://localhost:3002

| Method | Endpoint | Description     |
|--------|---------|-----------------|
| GET    | /courses | Get all courses |
| POST   | /courses | Add new course  |

