# ⚙️ Installation

Clone the repository:

git clone https://github.com/yourusername/node-microservices-tasks.git

Move into the project folder:

cd node-microservices-tasks

Install dependencies:

npm install

---

# 🧪 Environment Setup

Create .env file inside inventory-service:

MONGO_URI=mongodb://127.0.0.1:27017/inventoryDB

---

# ▶️ Running the Services

Open multiple terminals and run each service separately.

Terminal 1 – Inventory Service:

cd inventory-service
node server.js

Runs on:
http://localhost:3005

---

Terminal 2 – Store Service:

cd store-service
node server.js

Runs on:
http://localhost:3004

---

Terminal 3 – Course Service:

cd course-service
node server.js

Runs on:
http://localhost:3002

---

Terminal 4 – College Service:

cd college-service
node server.js

Runs on:
http://localhost:3003

---

# 🧪 API Testing

All APIs were tested using Postman.

Example:

POST http://localhost:3005/inventory

Body:

{
  "product": "Rice",
  "quantity": 50,
  "storeId": 1
}

